My university had a cron job and if your mailbox was too big it would be 
copied to your own directory and then be subject to your own quota's, 
meaning: you can't create any files until you deal with your mail...

The file was called oldmail, in the users own Mail directory, presumably, 
if it happended twice before they could deal with it, they'd loose the 
first lot.

